creator: Computer Language Company
descriptionHtml:
For nearly 40 years, the most comprehensive and easiest-to-understand high-tech dictionary. There is nothing like it.

FUNDAMENTALS for BEGINNERS. REINFORCEMENT for EXPERTS.

LEARN THE "CORRECT" LINGO AND TECH TERMS - TALK LIKE A PRO

EVERY IT CONCEPT BOILS DOWN TO SIMPLE BASICS, which are the underlying foundation in every definition.

FEATURES

* Instant search of more than 25,000 definitions about computers and consumer electronics. Zoom into noteworthy illustrations, photos, charts and diagrams. Every day, look up Tech Term of the Day (TTOD) for a random definition.

* Micro to mainframe: covers PCs, Macs, Unix, Linux, Internet, networking, broadband & telecom, fiber optics & lasers, major products and vendors, wireless & smartphones, acronyms, buzzwords, current topics, etc.

* Informative historical content and major product descriptions.

* Superior cross referencing and a powerful lookup engine.

Find out why PC Magazine gave us their highest dictionary award and Government Technology said we're the "Rolls Royce of Computer Dictionaries."

creator: Computer Language Company
descriptionHtml:
PLEASE NOTICE

We are experiencing crashes with the first versions of Android 11 and some earlier Android 10 versions.

We're trying to figure out what's going on, and until we do, we sincerely apologize for this inconvenience. You can always go to ComputerLanguage.com for definitions.

The bottom line is that too many programmers have been involved with this app, and the code has become messy. We have been offering the Android version to the community for more than a decade for free and without annoying ads. We financed the first five years of development, and volunteers kept it going after that. Unfortunately, they moved on to other projects, and although a programmer isolated the problem, we have yet to find a fix.

Sadly, we will likely have to drop this app because it is too difficult to maintain.


************************************************************************

creator: Computer Language Company
descriptionHtml:
PLEASE READ

For definitions, please go to ComputerLanguage.com.



In the near future, we are going to eliminate this Android app.


We have been experiencing crashes with the first versions of Android 11 and some earlier Android 10 versions.


It is becoming too difficult to maintain this app due to the OS changes that are constantly being made by the Android community.



For more than a decade, we have offered this app without charge and without annoying ads. We financed its development for the first six years, and programmers in India have volunteered to update the code for the past five. Unfortunately, they are no longer able to maintain the app due to the COVID crisis in their country.


We isolated these crashes and have had three programmers try to find a solution without success. Due to the many people who have added code over the years, the logic in this app is probably not straightforward, and very likely a mess. However, three years ago, we updated our website to accommodate all screen sizes, and ComputerLanguage.com works very well on small smartphone screens. In addition, the definitions are updated several times each month.



We hope you enjoy ComputerLanguage.com.


************************************************************************
